data.story: Tekniska Högskolans Studentkår, THS shared a page.
data.description:
We know that a lot of students can't find the motivation to exercise, the energy to study or the time to cook good food. We also know that a lot of us are stressed out, feel down or can’t sleep. These are all common problems due to the pressure from KTH and student life, which results in a lacking health among us students. But we can do something about that. THS presents: 

THS Health Week!

THS Health Week is an event focusing on food, lifestyle, mental and physical health. We want to explore and find new and easy ways for a healthier lifestyle in the everyday lives of us students.

THS Health Week is available for all students at KTH and features several lectures, activities and seminars, most for free. 

Click Like and get the latest news about the week and our events!

See you on May 9-12!

data.story: Tekniska Högskolans Studentkår, THS shared an event.
data.description:
Now it's time to cut your best plants to make sprouts, so that they are ready for the sprout-swop-day! The amount of sprouts you bring, you can take back home with you. 

The exchange will take place at Hyllan (by the microwaves) in Nymble. Between 17:00 and 17:30 you hand in your sprouts so that we will have a lot of beautiful sprouts to chose from when the exchange starts. While you wait, you can study the range of plants, mingle or have a fika at the café. For every sprout you hand in, you will get a ticket that will be swoped for the sprouts you would like to have. The exchange starts at 17:30 and will go on to 18:30. 

To make it easy to know what plant the sprout will grow into be, please mark your sprouts with the name of the plant. 

You can hand in any type of sprout, in a plastic bag with only wet paper or in a small pot, completely new from the plant or older with their own root systems, as long it will stay alive during the day, any solution is good. We hope that a lot of you will come and bring a lot of beautiful sprouts!

LAST DAY TO APPLY! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Josefin Berglund, Team Leader: Banquet Logistics 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
I was the Team Leader of Banquet logistics.

# What was the best part of your position?
To operate as a problem solver during the banquet evening was really challenging and FUN! But also the great feedback afterwards from our guests. 

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
To grow as an individual, to test your strength and skills, and to realize how much you actually can manage! I had so much fun last year that I wanted to be a part of it all again, this time as a member of the project core group!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

data.message:
1 DAY LEFT! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Michel Tabari, Back End Developer 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was a Back End Developer. I was one of two developers working on the server side code and API structure.

# What was the best part of your position?
- Learning a lot of new things and putting that knowledge into something meant for the real world, instead of just school assignments. Getting the chance to work with skilled and creative people that I could learn from!

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- I made new friends that I still hang out with today. The best part of being a project member of THS Armada is that you get the chance to work on something really big and real. You get to meet people from outside of your chapter, and you really grow as an individual. Besides that you get to network a lot with future employers!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

1 DAY LEFT! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Emelie Borg, Team Leader: Career Fair 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was the Team Leader for the Career Fair.

# What was the best part of your position?
- To work so closely with many inspiring students from different chapters. I had a fantastic journey with the group of Team Leaders and with my group of Career Fair hosts. I also got the chance to expand my competence and skills by getting into situations that I’d never experienced before.

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- It is a fantastic journey to be part of and it really is something that every KTH student should experience! The year as Team Leader for the Career Fair has given me friends and experiences that will last for my entire life! One thing you can be certain of when applying for a position is that everything is possible and that when you work with THS Armada, the most important thing is to have fun!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

1,5 days left! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Emil Plynning, Team Leader: Logistics Task Force 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was the Team Leader of the Logistics Task Force.

# What was the best part of your position?
- Solving problems quickly during time pressure, and to see the actual importance of my work, from a logistics point of view. 

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- THS Armada is an opportunity to get to meet new people, but above all else it is a chance to try on a position you’ve never had before, which is fun and a great way to grow as an individual!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

2 DAYS LEFT! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet William Brink, Banquet Technical Coordinator 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was the Banquet Technical Coordinator. 

# What was the best part of your position?
- The responsibility! Very fun and rewarding to get the opportunity of being responsible of the planning for the grand Banquet - the best event of THS Armada! - together with the rest of the Banquet team. 

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- Partly because there are many opportunities for responsibility within the project, but above all: All the great people you get to know!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

2,5 DAYS LEFT! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Axl Elisson, Graphic Designer 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was one of the Graphic Designers, my main task was to create graphic material for the events and the career fair. 

# What was the best part of your position?
- Above all else, I worked with the layout for THS Armada’s insertion in Osqledaren. The best part of this task was that I, together with the existing Copywriter, got to coordinate and design the entire layout of the insertion from scratch. Since there weren’t any previous versions, I got to really explore my creativity! 

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- At some point of your education, you should engage yourself as a project member of THS Armada. It is an incredibly cool and meritorious project, partly because of it’s size, but headmost because THS Armada is all about what is of most importance for us students: Finding a future employer. Beyond this, you get to meet amazing people from other chapters, something I hadn’t experienced during my four years at KTH.

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

2,5 days left! The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Sara Österberg, Photo Group Leader 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was the Photo Group Leader.

# What was the best part of your position?
- It was a very social position! I met every single one of the THS Armada project members during the days of the project member shoot, and all visitors at the events and the career fair. The Photo Group is present at all THS Armada related events! I loved combining administrative and creative work tasks. 

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- To get to know all the committed students, you really get a lot of friends! My advice is to challenge yourself with a position you’ve never tried before, for great personal development.

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

SHAPE THE ARMADA!

The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! THS Armada is Scandinavia's biggest career fair for students, and the largest student driven organization at KTH. Being a project member will guarantee finding lots of amazing friends from the entire KTH, and opportunities for a great amount of fun. In addition to this, every future employer you will meet will know about THS Armada. Great experience for your CV!

There are open positions in various fields: Business relations and Events, Logistics and Fair, Media and Communication and IT. This means that you can choose a position according to your interest! Since THS Armada is such a big and well established platform, there are great opportunities for you to really make something great out of your position. 

Are you interested in design and interior decoration? Why not design the entire THS Armada Banquet or our Green Room concept, which highlights our focus on sustainability! Are you really into IT? Why not develop our very own Android and iOS application! Do you love problem solving and being a hero while handling unexpected tasks? Why not become the Team Leader of the Logistics or Technical Task Force! Does PR appeal to your interest? Why not indulge yourself in working as one of our Marketing Coordinators! When working with THS Armada, not even sky is the limit!


Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

data.message:
The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. Meet Oliver Kling, Team Leader: Banquet Interior 2015!

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was the Team Leader of Banquet interior. My main tasks included interior design and decoration, as well as purchasing. 

# What was the best part of your position?
- The creative part was the best. Immediately I fell for the concept of designing such a big space according to my visions, and doing it along with the rest of the Banquet Team Leaders. It was magical, seeing how well it turned out and the experience we got to give to the visitors. Everything went perfectly according to the time schedule, after months of planning!

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- The best part of THS Armada was to leave the chapter of my programme for a while, and see what THS had to offer outside of it. The welcoming atmosphere and joy from the other KTH campus areas represented in the group of THS Armada turned out to be fantastic!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

The recruitment of Team Leaders, Developers, Coordinators and Creators of THS Armada 2016 is open until this Friday, 22nd of April! We would like to present some of the over 300 people who Shaped the Armada last year. First out: Beata Törneman, Team Leader: Lounges.

# What position did you have in THS Armada 2015?
- I was one of the Lounges Team Leader. Together with my co-Team Leader I was in charge of the two business lounges during the days of the career fair.

# What was the best part of your position?
- I loved my position, it suited me perfectly! I really enjoyed planning and setting up the lounges as we pictured them. In the beginning, I found it a bit challenging to make calls to find sponsors, but I got comfortable with it along the way. At the end it was really cool to see how great it all turned out! As Team Leaders, we were in charge of 12 hosts, which was the most fun part! We turned into a very close-knit group and had a very enjoyable time together!

# Why should you engage yourself in THS Armada?
- Because it’s the most enjoyable project you can be part of during your studies! You will get to know so many great and wonderful people who you get to keep for the rest of your life, and in addition to that you will learn how to take responsibility and grow as an individual!

Shape the Armada, send us your application before this Friday! All information about the open positions at http://armada.nu/#/recruitment.

The Project Group is longing to get inspired by your talent and skill! Look into our open Group Leader, Developer, Coordinator and Creator positions to find out what you should be doing this year. Shape the Armada, send us your application! All information is available at recruitment.armada.nu. Remember to apply no later than 22 of April.
